  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed rear dormer by reason of its siting and location would interrupt the existing predominantly unaltered roofline and be a dominant and incongruous addition within the terrace disrupting its rhythm and unity. The proposed dormer window would be harmful to the character and appearance of the host building, wider terrace setting and the surrounding conservation area being readily visible from the surrounding private realm. The proposal is therefore contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework 2021, Policies D1, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan 2021, Policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011, Policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Islington Development Management Policies 2013 and to the guidance within the Islington Urban Design Guide 2017, and the Tufnell Park Conservation Area Design Guidelines."
